args: After the flower shop, Addis and Helena's date\nproceeds smoothly. And it turns out time really\ndoes fly when one is having fun...
I can't believe it's evening already!\nAddis, would you mind terribly if\nwe visited this one last shop?
Welcome, friends! We deal in all manner\nof strange and unusual items in this shop.\nDo let me know if I can help find anything.
Well, I'll be damned. They even got\na couple'a things from Hinomoto.
What is this beautiful paper used for?
That's called origami paper. Folks in\nHinomoto fold it into various shapes\nto entertain each other.
Never thought to see its like around here.\nHey, shopkeep! I'll take a sheet.
So you fold it like this, and here, and...\nAll done. See? It's a rose.
Yeah, it's a neat little trick.\nHere, you can have this one.
Thank you so much! Er, but to be honest,\nthere's something I want to give you...
This is the rose you bought\nback at that first flower shop!
Consider it my way of saying thank you\nfor a wonderful day—as well as an\napology for being so selfish.
You made it clear this date held little\ninterest for you, yet I persisted and\nforced you into it. That was wrong.
You don't gotta apologize for that.
Hee hee! Well, it's good to know\nthat my eyes haven't failed me.
It means I'm glad the man I fell for at\nfirst blush turned out to be so nice.
I'm a lot of things, but I dunno\nthat ＂nice＂ is one of 'em.
It most certainly is! Most men would\nrefuse a date with a woman they've\nalready rejected out of hand.
To be honest, I could hardly believe the\nwords coming out of my mouth that day.
Coulda fooled me! I didn't see any way\nyou were gonna take no for an answer.
And when you accepted, that made it feel\nall the more like a dream come true.
But now it's time to wake from my dream.\nSo thank you again for a wonderful day.\nThis will be the last time you need see me.
Look, at least lemme walk you home.
Oh, there's still plenty of light;\nI think I can get home by myself.
And honestly, if we spend any more time\ntogether, it...it will be that much harder\nfor me to part from you.
Wait, so you actually don't know?\nFigured you'd be camped out in the\nbushes with a spyglass the whole time.
We most certainly were not! How rude!\n...Also, we couldn't take the chance you'd\nsee us and get distracted again.
Ooo, what a pretty rose!\nIs that from Helena?
You sound a little deflated there, bud.\nWhat's up? Did something happen?
Liar! Stop being coy and give it up.
I told you, it's nothin'. Just...
Well, on the way back, I started thinkin'\nthat maybe I'd been...cruel.
Looks like they dropped something...\nWhat the heck? It's an origami rose.
Listen well, peons of the Boar Clan!\nWe who lurk ever in the shadows\nhave taken your precious Helena.
The life of the seventh prince. If you wish\nto save the girl, you will bring us his head.
Some ninja you are! Why don't you just\ngo assassinate him your damn self?!
Are you truly too large a fool to see?\nThere is great value in having your hand\nbe the one to strike the killing blow.
You wanna dirty my hands in order to\nstain Ieyasu's reputation. That it?
Which means you're tryin' to overthrow\nmy master and maybe even take over\nthis country in the process.
You can save only his reputation or this\nwoman's life. Which will you choose?
Or I take the third option and cut down\nall you filthy cowards! Haaaaah!
Did you really think to take me down\nwith so feeble an attack?
Bring the prince's head to the\nWestern Woods before dawn!
They got away. If only I had my bow...
I'm so sorry, Addis. I screwed up.\nEr, so what's the plan?
I'm gonna chase these guys down and\nsave Helena. You go find that protector\nfella and watch the prince's back.
＂Protector fellow?＂ Wait, you mean Orion?\nWhy not just get the whole Halidom to—
'Cause they'll make too much noise.\nIf the ninjas realize what we're up to,\nthey'll kill Helena on the spot.
And if anyone's used to protectin'\nfolks on the down-low, it's that guy.
Gotcha. Then you go save Helena\nand leave {player_name} to us!
